'''Ali Imam''' (born 31 December 1950) is a [[Bangladesh|Bangladeshi]] children's writer and audio-visual organizer. He written a lots of scientificc story, travel stories for children. He was awarded [[Bangla Academy Literary Award]] in 2001 in juvenile literature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://banglaacademy.org.bd/?page_id=1315|title=পুরস্কারপ্রাপ্তদের তালিকা|language=bn|trans-title=Winners list|accessdate=23 August 2017|publisher=Bangla Academy}}</ref>

==Childhood==
Imam was born in [[Brahmanbaria District|Brahmanbaria]]. After six months of his birth, his whole family shifted to [[Dhaka]]. He spent his childhood in Nawabpur, Lincoln road, Thataribazar of [[Old Dhaka]].

==Works==
{{wide image|Panorama of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Novo Theatre.JPG|500px|[[Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Novo Theatre]] designed by architect Ali Imam.|45%|right
|alt=Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Novo Theatre}}
Imam has written more than 630 books, translated nearly 40. [[Child psychology]], humanism and adventure is found in his writing.

Imam was the  General Manager of Bangladesh Television and retired from the job in 2006.

