{{Template: English language}}
'''Bay Islands English''' is an English variety spoken on the [[Bay Islands Department]] ([[Guanaja]], [[Roatán]], [[Utila]]), Honduras. 22,500 native speakers ([[Caracoles]]) were reported in 2001.<ref>{{Ethnologue20|eng|English language (Honduras)}}</ref> Mainlanders know this language as ''Caracol'', which literally means "[[conch]]". Genetically this variety descends from [[Cayman Islands English]].

