Along with learners and other Esperantists of all levels, many very experienced Esperantists and [[native Esperantists]] have joined the project. At least three editors are members of the [[Academy of Esperanto]], [[Gerrit Berveling]], [[John C. Wells]], and [[Bertilo Wennergren]], a notable Esperanto grammarian<ref>{{lang|eo|[http://bertilow.com/pmeg/libro.html Plena Manlibro de Esperanta Gramatiko}}] by Bertilo Wennergren.</ref> and the director of the Academy's section about Esperanto [[vocabulary]].

{{lang|eo|Vikipedio}} incorporates, with permission, the content of the 1934 {{lang|eo|[[Encyclopedia of Esperanto|Enciklopedio de Esperanto]]}} and also content from several reference books and the monthly periodical {{lang|eo|[[Monato]]}}.

The Esperanto Wikipedia has been featured in many Esperanto news media, including a radio interview at [[Radio Polonia]],<ref>https://archive.org/details/UnuaIntervjuoKunChuckSmithPriVikipedio Interview with Chuck Smith in Esperanto about the Esperanto Wikipedia</ref> and articles at {{lang|eo|Esperanto}}, {{lang|eo|[[Kontakto]]}}, {{lang|eo|[[Libera Folio]]}}<ref>{{lang|eo|[http://www.liberafolio.org/2007/antverpenviki/ Vikipedio kreskas kiam Antverpeno festas — Libera Folio, 2007]}}</ref> and {{lang|eo|Raporto.info}}.<ref>{{lang|eo|[https://web.archive.org/web/20070510074149/http://raporto.info/2007/03/18/vikipedio-la-reta-esperanta-enciklopedio-progresas/ Raporto.info » Vikipedio, la reta esperanta enciklopedio progresas, 2007]}}</ref> The [[Esperanto Wikimania]], a gathering held in 2011 to celebrate the encyclopedia's 10th anniversary, has been subsidized by the host city of [[Svitavy]] ([[Czech Republic]]) and the [[Pardubice Region]] and covered by [[Czech Television]].<ref>[http://www.transparent.com/esperanto/esperanto-wikimania-in-svitavy/ Smith, Chuck: ''Esperanto Wikimania in Svitavy'' In ''Esperanto Language Blog'']</ref><ref>''Ve Svitavách se sešli tvůrci Wikipedie v esperantu'' In ''Události v regionech (Brno)''. Česká televize. 2011-10-27, 18:00. [http://www.ceskatelevize.cz/ivysilani/10122427178-udalosti-v-regionech-brno/311281381991027-udalosti-v-regionech/obsah/175875-ve-svitavach-se-sesli-tvurci-wikipedie-v-esperantu/ Available on-line]</ref>

Esperanto organisations like [[Universal Esperanto Association]] do not contribute to {{lang|eo|Vikipedio}} but support it by providing chambers at Esperanto conventions for {{lang|eo|Vikipedio}} presentations and trainings. At the [[World Esperanto Congress]] in Rotterdam, summer 2008, there were two Wikipedian meetups and a lecture at the Esperantology Conference. In April 2013, [[:meta:Esperanto kaj Libera Scio|ELiSo]] (''Esperanto and Free Knowledge'') was established as one of the first [[Wikimedia Foundation|Wikimedia]] user groups.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Affiliations_Committee/Resolutions/Esperanto_kaj_Libera_Scio_%E2%80%93_March_2013|title=Affiliations Committee/Resolutions/Esperanto kaj Libera Scio – March 2013|publisher=|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>

=== Wikipedia handbook in Esperanto ===
The Esperanto Wikipedia community has created and published a 40-page "Wikipedia: Practical Handbook" ({{lang|eo|Vikipedio: Praktika Manlibro}}) which is sold on-line and at conventions.<ref>{{lang|eo|[http://www.esperanto.be/fel/but/lib/mvik.php Vikipedio: praktika manlibro]}}</ref> The manual is intended to give new Wikipedians advice and information on how to edit Wikipedia in Esperanto. It is currently in its second printing.

